[1
Date: Thu, 26 Oct 2000 10:54:07 +0200
From: Jan ter Meulen <termeulen@mailer.uni-marburg.de>

Yesterday 3 serum samples were reported positive for yellow fever IgM
antibodies by Christian Mathiot, IP Dakar. The MoH and WHO Guinea
are arranging for YF vaccination in the affected region.
This outbreak of a febrile jaundice in Mamou district, Republic of
Guinea, was investigated by a joint team of the Ministry of Health
(MoH), Guinea, and the "Projet de Recherche sur les Fievres
Hemorragiques en Guinee" (PFHG), Conakry, Guinea. Barrier nursing
measures were implemented in the regional hospital of Mamou, and
contacts of patients were investigated.
Serum samples are being analysed by the PFHG in Conakry, the Pasteur
Institute Dakar, Senegal, the Pasteur Institute Paris, France, and the
Institute of Virology, Marburg, Germany.
--
J. ter Meulen, MD, DTM&H (London)
Institute of Virology, Philipps Univ.
