Date: Thu, 26 Oct 2000 07:41:22 +0200
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

GIDEON <http://www.cyinfo.com> tells me that Guinea lies within the
yellow fever "Endemic Zone," and that one case was reported in 1952
and none during 1953 to 1986.
The last cases (5) were reported in 1987.
Potential for infection exists in the Siguiri region. Proof of vaccination
IS required for travelers over 1 year of age arriving from infected areas.
